com.antigenomics.alisa.algebra.matrix

Class Matrix

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.antigenomics.alisa.algebra.matrix.Matrix
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Container<IndexedMatrixValue,Matrix>, ImmutableLinearSpaceObject<Matrix>, LinearSpaceObject<Matrix>, TypedCloneable<Matrix>, VectorMapping<Vector,Matrix>, Encoding, Representation, Serializable, Iterable<IndexedMatrixValue>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    DenseMatrix, DenseTriangularMatrix, SparseMatrix

    public abstract class Matrix
extends Object
implements LinearSpaceObject<Matrix>, VectorMapping<Vector,Matrix>, Container<IndexedMatrixValue,Matrix>
    A generic two-dimensional real vector. The storage type (dense/sparse) depends on implementation. Based on the storage type, fast access is implemented either via getAt (dense) or iterator (sparse) functions. This class supports all linear algebra operations and can compute linear and bilinear forms if supplied with Vector objects. This class implements basic checks to guarantee that the dimensions of two matrices are matched for operations where it is required. Linear algebra methods tagged as in-place are not guaranteed to be thread safe.

    Serialized Form
